Regional missives from filmmaker Tania Feghali, whose work focuses on music, the poetry of journeying and documentary.
From the host: "In Contrary Motion – mainly piano pieces, echoes, fragments and glimpses of music as a continuous movement. Featuring Jessica Williams, Mary Lou Williams, Tomita, Tsegué Maryam Gebrou, Toshiko Akiyoshi, Friedrich Gulda, Terry Riley, Natalie Beylis, Haruomi Hosono, Moondog, Precious Tucker & others."

Monthly vibrance & light from the Chicago based composer, pianist, clarinetist & jazz oracle.
From the host: "Music journalist and “Rhythm Analyst” DeForrest Brown Jr. joins Angel to debrief about their show together at Western Front. Plus, a special 30-minute Alkebulan playlist curated by DeForrest, featuring vibrant sounds from the homeland. Tune in for an inspiring blend of music, culture & conversation."

nts1.n: NTS GUIDE TO: INDIAN CLASSICAL INFLUENCE ON JAZZ (R)
nts1.d: In the mid-1950s musicians such as Yusuf Lateef and John Coltrane started to use instruments, structure and patterns based on traditional Indian music.  Artists sought to expand the boundaries of jazz by incorporating the modal structures, improvisational depth, and spiritual ethos of Indian music. Listen to two hours of Jazz inspired by Indian Classical.

From the host: "2025, what a trip! Here's my annual musical digest of the year just gone

LABOUR is the duo of Colin Hacklander and Farahnaz Hatam. Tune in each month for their hour-long show featuring rotating guests and friends from Dakar, Senegal. Expect a mixture of progressive electronic music with heavy sabar drum music, classic & current Mbalax, and timeless Sufi praises.
From the host: "This show follows on up the last here from October 2025, and features the great Senegalese singer & bandleader, Ouzin Ndiaye, known for his work with Youssou Ndour who features on several tracks of this show, but as a backup vocalist!"

Mr. Big Happy is a graphic designer, artist, DJ, and music archivist from San Francisco, California. While he is an accomplished designer and artist, over the years he has always had a love for music and spends time searching for rare and obscure vinyl. Big Happy’s focus is the late 70s into the late 80s - modern soul, funk, boogie and disco.
High speed electronics and dance soundtracks from the Chicago footwork auteur.
Two hours of electro, jit and ghetto-tech anthems from one of Detroit's premier party labels.
Renegade Soundwaves by Pandora's Jukebox: sonic assemblages with hypnotic noir-dreamscapes and a multi-textured take on electronic music.
Todmorden's finest, Kim Lana joins us in the Manchester studio once a month for 2 hours of bumping and pumping golden era house & techno.

Cultural virtuoso and creative luminary SHABAZZ, aka DJ Auntie Spice, illuminates obscure nostalgic treasures, crafting a rich, diverse auditory experience of soul, funk, jazz and beyond with her sound art initiative, Auntie·ism.

Jazz multi-instrumentalist Eric Dolphy was a key figure in jazz's leap into the avant-garde in the early 1960s alongside Ornette Coleman, and was an experimental influence on John Coltrane as member of his touring band. 
His nascent "free jazz" style featured ecstatic, lengthy improvisations that defied musical logic, non-musical speech-like sound. He also pioneered bass clarinet as a solo jazz instrument.
Bi-monthly emissions from Conrad Standish and Sam Karmel, aka CS + Kreme - keeping it loose, deep and free.

subtle.d:
Hailing from Mumbai, now living in London, Chaitu is energised by the UK sound and scene.

With a love of all things weird, weighty and groovy; his mixes and productions bridge electro, techno, breaks, UKG and Jungle, with sprinklings of everything in between.

Chaitu champions provocative beats that break down the barriers of style, genre and expectation, all while keeping you moving.

Saraphim (aka RNS & RDubz) are two Essex based Producer/DJ’s currently focused on Dubstep & the 140 spectrum, mixing ethnical and grime influences into their music. You can expect anything from deep and melodic meditative vibes to high energy driven music.
London based DJ who enjoys exploring the darker, bassier corners of Jungle, Breaks, Techno and Drum & Bass, especially when it is laced with a bit of acid.

Wheel2Wheel is a Manchester based event which primarily focuses on the underground sectors to genres such as UK Garage, House, Tech House, Electro, Minimal and Breakbeat. Co-Founder Freddie SJ hosts the first hour of the show, sharing his favourites as well as recent digs across the genres, and then invites fellow friends, artists and nights from the scene to present hour-long guest mixes which aims to shine a light on their sound and who they are!


With hours of Discogs screen-time under his belt and a passion for 90's & early 00's releases, expect to hear a variety of different tunes from Labels you may have never heard of and Countries you might not expect!


Give us a follow on Instagram to hear about our upcoming events and all other things music related! @wheel2wheel.mcr

subtle.n: The Ice Box Sessions with Frigid

subtle.d: Japanese DJ from Tokyo, currently living in London.  Based on UK club music, but straddles other genres such as dancehall, reggaeton, gqom and amapiano.

Hailing from northern Italy, STANDARD is a collective of artists, DJs and producers that aims at the promotion of bass music: Garage, UK Funky, Breaks, Leftfield Bass, Leftfield Techno, Dubstep, everything in between and beyond. They focus on the Italian Bass scene, showcasing new up-and-coming artists as well as established talents from all over the peninsula.

Oddkut is a producer & DJ hailing from Balakovo City, Russia. He's part of the Russian collective "United Gang" who are a Moscow-based community of local musicians, DJ's and promoters teamed up by their genuine love & interest in UK underground music, "TAЭT VREMYA" art group and the creator of the Moscow parties "Judder".

Kishan is a DJ and Producer currently based in London. Actively involved in the music scene already, he produces and mixes a wide range of genres including UK Garage, Drum & Bass, House, Disco and Afrobeat.
